On Saturday, April 4, the Tax Amazon campaign hosted a virtual signature gathering launch for ballot initiative I-131.
“This is not a new crisis for working people,” said Matt, “It’s an acceleration of an existing crisis, where working people are living paycheck to paycheck.
To get our tax on the ballot, we need a powerful online and phone-banking outreach campaign to collect 30,000 signatures from Seattle voters in the coming months.
Winning this campaign, even just winning the fight to get Tax Amazon on the ballot, will be an uphill battle.
Tax Amazon provides our movements with the answer: Make big business pay for the crisis of their system, not working people!